      "content": "exactly. it's just a biological glitch, basically. our brains are forced to keep fighting and feeling things that don't actually matter in the grand scheme of anything. it feels so heavy sometimes, just carrying around all this weight and anxiety for a life that has no objective purpose. if biology is just forcing us to endure this unnecessary noise, it makes me wonder if there's any actual logic in just... not participating anymore. if the outcome is always nothingness, then what's the point in staying in the struggle?",
